node.text:
We're hiring Web developers and Graphic designers for interns!

" Open to all UG students "

Web developers should have experience in any one of following -  HTML, CSS, JS, PHP and modern frameworks like React.js and Next.js .

Graphic designers should be familiar with any one of the following - Photoshop, Illustrator, CorelDRAW, Premiere Pro, FCPX and After effects.

We shall be deploying you on live projects and events. 

You will be learning a lot!

Mail your Resume/CV and work samples to pattarai.licet@gmail.com

Letter of Recommendation and Certificates will also be provided.

With regards,
LICET PATTARAI.

node.text:
There are three parts to the project:

Drive a rover using a Raspberry Pi

Detect objects using Tensorflow Lite and Mobilenet-SSD (Single Shot Detection)

Track a specified object class (eg. person or bird) using a pan-tilt camera with Proportional Integral Derivative (PID) process control

This is the required hardware for the project:

Raspberry Pi 4B (at least 2GB recommended)

Robot Car Chassis

TT Motor + Wheel X 2

4xAA battery holder

Acrylic board to hold everything together

L298N Motor Driver (Used to control the motors)

5MP Camera for Raspberry Pi

FFC Cable longer than 20cm (as you will need to move your camera around)

SG90 Micro Servo X 2 (to pan/tilt camera)

All Credit :🎥@coding_essentials
